cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.ED 

This paper focuses on a web-based writing and revising environment that uses natural language processing features to provide formative feedback on students' use of evidence in response-to-text writing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as natural language processing is a key component of these fields. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as these fields deal with the processing and analysis of large amounts of data. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the field of Education (cs.ED) as it discusses the use of technology to improve student writing skills.
